## Project

`lateral-travel` — Booking.com-style app for curated remote-work stays. Frontend-only; MSW intercepts `/api/*` (dev + production).

Live: https://lateral-travel.vercel.app

## Tech stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript (strict)
- **Package manager**: pnpm (npm/yarn/bun also work)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4
- **UI**: shadcn/ui primitives in `components/ui/` (built on `@base-ui/react`)
- **Server state**: TanStack Query v5 — no Redux, RTK Query, or Zustand
- **Forms**: React Hook Form + Zod (user input only)
- **API mock**: MSW 2.x
- **Testing**: Vitest + Testing Library; colocated `*.spec.ts(x)`
- **Lint**: oxlint

## Project structure

Single Next.js app — **not** an Nx monorepo. Import alias: `@/*` → repo root.

```
app/                    # routes only — thin page shells + Suspense
  page.tsx              # /
  stays/[stayId]/       # stay detail
  checkout/
  bookings/[bookingId]/ # confirmation

features/               # one folder per domain
  stays/ | reviews/ | bookings/ | home/
  api/types/            # shared ApiError types
  <domain>/
    api/                # *-api.ts (apiFetch) + use-*-queries.ts (TanStack hooks)
    components/         # screens + UI; *.skeleton.tsx for loading states
    domain/ | utils/    # plain business logic — no React, no HTTP
    types/              # request/response shapes (API contract, client + mock)
    hooks/              # domain hooks (e.g. URL-driven filter state)

components/
  ui/                   # shared shadcn primitives
  layout/               # site-header, page-shell, content-container

lib/                    # api-client, format helpers, cn()
mocks/                  # handlers → repositories → seeded in-memory data
tests/                  # shared test setup (MSW server, renderWithQueryClient)
```

## Architecture

**Data flow (one direction):**

`component → query hook → *-api.ts → apiFetch → HTTP → MSW handler → repository → domain logic`

**Do:**

- Keep `app/` pages thin — compose `features/*/components`, wrap async UI in `<Suspense>`
- Put HTTP in `features/<domain>/api/*-api.ts`; TanStack hooks in `use-*-queries.ts` with `queryKey` factories
- Share types via `features/<domain>/types/` — same shapes on client and mock server
- Keep pricing, filtering, sorting as plain functions in `domain/` or `utils/`
- Store search/filter state in the URL (`useSearchParams`), not component state
- Throw `ApiError` from `lib/api-client/api-client.ts` on failed requests
- Use Zod for form schemas only; trust API responses via TypeScript types

**Don't:**

- Build URLs or read mock data directly from components
- Add global state — TanStack Query caches server data, RHF owns forms
- Parse API responses with Zod
- Put testable business logic inside components or MSW handlers

## Testing

- MSW runs globally (`tests/setup.ts`); unhandled requests fail tests
- Use `renderWithQueryClient` from `@/tests/render-with-query-client` for components using queries
- Override handlers per test with `server.use(...)` when needed
- Prefer accessible queries (`getByRole`, `getByLabelText`) and `userEvent.setup()`
- Domain/utils: test plain functions directly; no MSW needed

## Commands

| Script | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `pnpm dev` | Dev server (MSW auto-starts) |
| `pnpm lint` | oxlint |
| `pnpm typecheck` | `tsc --noEmit` |
| `pnpm test` | vitest run |
| `pnpm build` | production build |

